VALUES
(43, 4, 34, 18, 23, 12, 12, 'my meat is to do the will', 'Connection of Spiritual Sustenance', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of spiritual nourishment over physical sustenance. Jesus speaks of doing the will of God as his ''meat,'' while Job values God''s commandments more than ''necessary food.''', 'theme', 0.503, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 34, 40, 26, 39, 39, NULL, 'Connection of Divine Will', 'This connection highlights the theme of submitting to God''s will. In John 4:34, Jesus expresses his commitment to doing the will of God, while in Matthew 26:39, he prays for God''s will to be done, despite his own desires.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 34, 42, 19, 10, 10, 'to do the will of him that sent me', 'Connection of Mission and Purpose', 'Both passages emphasize the mission of Jesus to fulfill God''s will. John 4:34 highlights doing the will of God, while Luke 19:10 focuses on seeking and saving the lost, which aligns with that purpose.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 34, 19, 40, 8, 8, 'to do the will of him that sent me', 'Connection of Divine Will', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of doing God''s will. Jesus expresses his commitment to fulfill the work of God, while the psalmist delights in doing God''s will, indicating a shared theme of obedience and purpose.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 34, 42, 15, 10, 10, 'to do the will of him that sent me', 'Joy in Doing God''s Will', 'This connection highlights the theme of fulfilling God''s purpose. Both passages emphasize the importance of repentance and completing the work assigned by God, suggesting that doing His will brings joy.', 'theme', 0.377, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 35, 42, 10, 2, 3, 'for they are white already to harvest', 'Harvest and Laborers Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the urgency of the harvest and the need for laborers. John highlights that the fields are ''white already to harvest,'' while Luke notes that ''the harvest truly is great, but the labourers are few.''', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 35, 40, 9, 37, 38, 'harvest', 'Harvest and Laborers Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the urgency of the harvest and the need for laborers. John 4:35 highlights that the fields are ready for harvest, while Matthew 9:37-38 notes the plenteous harvest and the few laborers available.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 35, 43, 4, 30, 30, 'look on the fields; for they are white already to harvest', 'Harvest and Response', 'Both passages emphasize the urgency of the harvest. The people coming to Jesus in John 4:30 can be seen as a response to the call to look on the fields that are ready for harvest in John 4:35.', 'theme', 0.293, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 36, 59, 5, 19, 20, 'gathereth fruit unto life eternal', 'Reaping and Saving Souls', 'This connection highlights the theme of reaping and gathering fruit, as both passages discuss the importance of converting others and the resulting eternal rewards. The act of converting a sinner is akin to reaping, leading to the saving of souls and eternal life.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 36, 45, 1, 13, 13, 'gathereth fruit unto life eternal', 'Reaping and Gathering Fruit', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of gathering fruit, with John highlighting the joy of those who reap and Romans expressing a desire for fruit among the Gentiles. This connection highlights the shared theme of spiritual harvest and the joy in collective efforts.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 36, 46, 3, 5, 9, 'he that soweth and he that reapeth', 'Laborers in God''s Harvest', 'Both passages emphasize the roles of sowing and reaping in ministry, highlighting that those who labor together in God''s work will receive rewards. The idea of rejoicing together in the harvest connects the themes of collaboration and divine increase.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 36, 20, 11, 30, 30, 'fruit unto life eternal', 'Connection of Righteousness and Reaping', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''fruit'' as a reward for righteous actions. John 4:36 speaks of gathering fruit unto life eternal, while Proverbs 11:30 describes the fruit of the righteous as a tree of life, linking the ideas of spiritual harvest and wisdom in winning souls.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 36, 55, 4, 7, 8, 'fruit unto life eternal', 'Eternal Rewards for Faithfulness', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of receiving rewards for faithful service. In John 4:36, the idea of gathering fruit unto life eternal connects to the crown of righteousness mentioned in 2 Timothy 4:8.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 36, 27, 12, 3, 3, 'that both he that soweth and he that reapeth may rejoice together', 'Reaping and Righteousness Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of reward for those who lead others to righteousness. Both passages emphasize the joy and eternal significance of gathering fruit and turning many to righteousness.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 36, 45, 6, 22, 22, 'fruit unto life eternal', 'Fruit and Everlasting Life', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''fruit'' leading to eternal outcomes. John speaks of gathering fruit unto life eternal, while Romans describes fruit unto holiness resulting in everlasting life.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 37, 33, 6, 15, 15, 'One soweth, and another reapeth', 'Sowing and Reaping Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of sowing and reaping, where John 4:37 states that one sows while another reaps, and Micah 6:15 indicates that sowing will not lead to reaping. Both passages emphasize the futility of labor without reward.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 37, 18, 31, 8, 8, 'One soweth, and another reapeth.', 'Sowing and Reaping Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of sowing and the consequences that follow. In John 4:37, the idea of one sowing and another reaping reflects a broader theme of shared labor and outcomes, which resonates with Job 31:8''s mention of sowing and another eating.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 37, 7, 6, 3, 3, 'One soweth, and another reapeth.', 'Sowing and Reaping Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of sowing and reaping. In John 4:37, the idea of one sowing and another reaping reflects the consequences of actions, while Judges 6:3 illustrates the negative outcome of Israel''s sowing when the Midianites and Amalekites come to reap destruction.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 37, 42, 19, 21, 21, NULL, 'Sowing and Reaping Concept', 'Both passages emphasize the principle of sowing and reaping. John 4:37 speaks to the division of labor in harvesting, while Luke 19:21 reflects on reaping without having sown, highlighting the consequences of one''s actions.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 38, 43, 1, 7, 7, 'laboured', 'Witness and Labor Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of labor in spreading belief. Both passages emphasize the efforts of others in bringing the Light to the world, suggesting a continuity in the mission of witnessing and reaping the fruits of that labor.', 'theme', 0.356, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 38, 14, 36, 15, 15, 'other men laboured, and ye are entered into their labours', 'Compassion and Labor in Ministry', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine compassion and the labor involved in ministry. Both passages emphasize the idea of others having labored before, leading to the current opportunity to reap the benefits of that labor.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 38, 44, 10, 42, 43, 'ye are entered into their labours', 'Labor and Witness Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of labor in spreading the message of Jesus. In John, the disciples enter into the labors of others, while in Acts, they are commanded to testify about Jesus, emphasizing the continuation of this labor in preaching.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 38, 60, 1, 11, 12, 'ye are entered into their labours', 'Labor and Revelation Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of labor and revelation in both passages. John 4:38 speaks of entering into the labors of others, while 1 Peter 1:12 emphasizes that the prophets ministered for future generations, indicating a continuity of divine revelation and effort.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 38, 44, 8, 14, 17, 'ye are entered into their labours', 'Labor and Reception of the Spirit', 'This connection highlights the theme of entering into the labors of others. In John 4:38, Jesus speaks of reaping where others have labored, which parallels Acts 8:14-17, where the apostles build upon the work done in Samaria by praying for the new believers to receive the Holy Ghost.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 38, 40, 3, 1, 6, 'laboured, and ye are entered into their labours', 'Labor and Preparation for Ministry', 'This connection highlights the theme of labor in ministry. John the Baptist''s preparation of the way for Jesus reflects the ''labour'' of those who came before, as mentioned in John 4:38.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 38, 40, 11, 8, 13, 'ye are entered into their labours', 'Labor and Prophetic Preparation', 'This connection highlights the theme of labor in the context of prophetic ministry. Both passages emphasize the work done by others before, with John the Baptist serving as a key figure preparing the way for Jesus'' ministry.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 39, 43, 4, 29, 29, 'He told me all that ever I did', 'Connection of Testimony and Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the woman''s testimony about Jesus, specifically her claim that he told her all things that ever she did. This testimony leads many Samaritans to believe in him, highlighting the impact of personal witness on faith.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 39, 43, 4, 5, 5, 'Samaritans of that city believed', 'Connection of Belief and Location', 'This connection highlights the significance of the city of Sychar in the context of belief. The mention of the Samaritans believing in Jesus due to the woman''s testimony ties back to the specific location where this interaction took place.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 39, 43, 10, 41, 42, 'believed on him for the saying', 'Belief in Jesus'' Testimony', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of belief based on testimony. In John 4:39, the Samaritans believe because of the woman''s testimony, while in John 10:41-42, many believe based on John''s truthful words about Jesus.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 4, 39, 43, 4, 42, 42, 'He told me all that ever I did', 'Belief in Christ''s Testimony', 'This connection highlights the progression of belief among the Samaritans. Initially, they believed based on the woman''s testimony, but later affirmed their faith after hearing Jesus directly.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
